12 INCREASE CERTAIN MAXIMUM GROUP SIZES & REVISE NAP-TIME
13 SUPERVISION REQUIREMENTS IN CHILD CARE
14 SECTION 1.3. G.S. 110-91(7)a. reads as rewritten:
15 "a. The Commission shall adopt rules for child care centers regarding
16 staff-child ratios, group sizes and multi-age groupings other than for
17 infants and toddlers, provided that these rules shall be no less stringent
18 than those currently required for staff-child ratios as enacted in Section
19 156(e) of Chapter 757 of the 1985 Session Laws.
20 1. Except as otherwise provided in this subdivision, the minimum
21 staff-child ratios and group sizes for infants and toddlers in
22 child care centers shall be no less stringent than as follows:
23 Age Ratio Staff/Children Group Size
24 0 to 12 months 1/5 1015
25 12 to 24 months 1/6 1218
26 2 to 3 years 1/10 20.
27 No child care center shall care for more than 25 children in one
28 group. Child care centers providing care for 26 or more
29 children shall provide for two or more groups according to the
30 ages of children and shall provide separate supervisory
31 personnel and separate identifiable space for each group.
32 1a. If a child care center is operating under voluntary enhanced
33 requirements, the maximum group size for toddlers aged 2 to
34 3 years may be increased from 18 to 20 children when the child
35 care center maintains a 1/9 staff-child ratio.
36 1b. If a child care center is operating under the highest voluntary
37 enhanced requirements, the child care center may use the
38 following maximum group sizes for infants and toddlers when
39 the child care center maintains staff-child ratios as provided
40 herein:
41 Age Ratio Staff/Children Group Size
42 0 to 12 months 1/4 12
43 12 to 24 months 1/5 15
44 2 to 3 years 1/8 20.
45 1c. For groups of children 1 year of age or older, the staff-child
46 ratio during nap time shall comply with the requirements of
47 rules adopted by the Commission if (i) at least one person
48 remains in the room, (ii) all children are visible to that person,
49 and (iii) the total number of required staff are on the premises
50 and within calling distance of the rooms occupied by children.
51 …."
