12 SECTION 2.4. G.S. 110-98.5 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 110-98.5. Care for school-age children during state of emergency.
14 Notwithstanding any provision of law or rule to the contrary, when remote or virtual learning
15 is required due to a declared state of emergency issued under G.S. 166A-19.20, the following
16 shall apply:
17 …
18 (3) Care provided to school-age children pursuant to this section is not considered
19 child care as defined under G.S. 110-86. However, if a program was licensed
20 prior to the state of emergency, it shall be deemed licensed during the state of
21 emergency whether it expands its capacity to provide services to more
22 children so long as it adheres to the staff to child ratios for licensure."
23 SECTION 2.5. The Weikart Youth Program Quality Assessment (Weikart Program)
24 shall be added as an assessment tool for evaluating out-of-school child care programs and
25 awarding of a star rating. The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Child
26 Development and Early Education, shall complete the necessary crosswalk evaluation of the
27 Weikart Program and have it available for applicants to use not later than six months after the
28 date this act becomes law.
